{"id": "4239", "post": "<div class=\"post-4239 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-tutorials tag-tutorials-2\" id=\"post-4239\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/your-own-mail-server-with-virtualmin/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Your own mail server with Virtualmin</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/tutorials-2/\" rel=\"tag\">tutorials</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> August 24, 2013 @ 8:34 am, by Maarten Kossen</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/lowendtutorial.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/lowendtutorial.png.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3957 litespeed-loaded\" alt=\"lowendtutorial\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/lowendtutorial.png.webp\" width=\"271\" height=\"70\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a></p><p>In light of recent events, there\u2019s been a lot of chatter about leaving free e-mail services in favor of self-hosted e-mail. With self-hosted e-mail you have the option to host your e-mail wherever you want it, either on a server at home or on a VPS.</p><p>There\u2019s plenty of affordable options around to run your own mail server. I would personally recommend a Xen or KVM VPS for this, as with OpenVZ it is really easy for your provider to \u201csnoop\u201d on your e-mail. This is also possible with Xen or KVM, but it usually requires a reboot (which you will probably notice).</p><p>I\u2019ve used a 512MB Xen VPS for this tutorial. I\u2019ve used \u201cthis much\u201d memory because I want to run clamd and SpamAssassin in RAM. The server also has 45GB of disk space, which is more than enough to run a couple of big mailboxes on. You could do with less RAM (though that would increase the CPU load and slow down mail processing) and far less disk space (depending on your needs), but with \u201cmy\u201d specs, you\u2019re on the safe side.<br>\n<span id=\"more-4239\"></span></p><h2>Installing Virtualmin</h2><p>I\u2019m using Virtualmin in this tutorial.&nbsp;The choice for Virtualmin is quite easy: it\u2019s free, fast, stable and doesn\u2019t invade your system (like, for example, cPanel does). Virtualmin may not have the prettiest UI out there, but it\u2019s clean and it\u2019s effective. You\u2019ll only be using Virtualmin to create and administrate mailboxes. Other than that, you won\u2019t need it.</p><p>Virtualmin has an open source (GPL) version and a commercial version. The commercial version has some \u201cadvanced\u201d features not in the GPL version. I\u2019ll be using the GPL version. This should run on most Linux distributions and FreeBSD.</p><p>So let\u2019s install Virtualmin. I recommend a clean server for this,&nbsp; to avoid any conflicts. On the server, run:</p><blockquote><p>wget http://software.virtualmin.com/gpl/scripts/install.sh</p></blockquote><p>Which will get the installer script. Next, make it executable:</p><blockquote><p>chmod +x install.sh</p></blockquote><p>And finally, run the installer:</p><blockquote><p>sudo ./install.sh</p></blockquote><p>Which should ask you for your sudo password and if you\u2019re sure you\u2019re running the installer on a suitable system:</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mpkossen@leb001-_002.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mpkossen@leb001-_002.png.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-4240 litespeed-loaded\" alt=\"mpkossen@leb001: ~_002\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mpkossen@leb001-_002.png.webp\" width=\"521\" height=\"386\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mpkossen@leb001-_002.png.webp 868w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mpkossen@leb001-_002-300x222.png.webp 300w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 521px) 100vw, 521px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 521px) 100vw, 521px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mpkossen@leb001-_002.png.webp 868w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mpkossen@leb001-_002-300x222.png.webp 300w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a></p><p>Next, it\u2019s going to install a bunch of packages. Just sit back and relax. Get a cup of coffee or a beer. It could take anywhere from 5 tot 15 minutes (on average).</p><p>Once that is done, open a web browser and go to either your IP address or domain name on port 10000 with \u2018https\u2019 prepended:</p><blockquote><p>https://192.0.2.1:10000</p><p>https://leb001.example.net:10000/</p></blockquote><p>This should ask you to log in:</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Login-to-Webmin-Mozilla-Firefox_003.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4241\" alt=\"Login to Webmin - Mozilla Firefox_003\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Login-to-Webmin-Mozilla-Firefox_003.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Login-to-Webmin-Mozilla-Firefox_003.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Login-to-Webmin-Mozilla-Firefox_003-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Login-to-Webmin-Mozilla-Firefox_003-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Use the username and password of your sudo user to log in. Once logged in, the post-installation wizard should appear:</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_004.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4242\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_004\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_004.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_004.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_004-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_004-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Click \u2018Next\u2019. You will be asked whether to preload the virtualmin libraries or not and whether you want to run the email domain lookup server. I would recommend against the former, except if you have plenty of RAM. I would recommend turning on the domain lookup server for faster mail processing.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_006.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4243\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_006\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_006.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_006.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_006-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_006-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>In the next step you can enable the ClamAV mail scanner server. I would really recommend enabling this.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_007.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4244\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_007\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_007.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_007.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_007-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_007-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>The same applies to the SpamAssassin server filter in the next step. This one is easier on the memory than the ClamAV server or domain lookup server, so even in you choose not to enable those two, you should enable this one.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_008.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4245\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_008\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_008.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_008.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_008-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_008-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>We don\u2019t need MySQL or PostgreSQL running and sucking up memory. So disable both.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_009.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4246\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_009\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_009.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_009.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_009-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_009-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>We don\u2019t need bind, so tick the box to skip the resolvability check and leave the other fields the way they are.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_010.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4247\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_010\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_010.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_010.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_010-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_010-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Passwords should never, ever be stored in plain text, so only store hashed passwords.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_011.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4248\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_011\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_011.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_011.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_011-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_011-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Click \u2018Next\u2019 to go to the \u2018System Information\u2019 screen.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_012.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4249\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_012\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_012.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_012.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_012-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_012-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Which should look like this (don\u2019t mind the yellow warning, we\u2019ll get to that):</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_013.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4250\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_013\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_013.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_013.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_013-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_013-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>You\u2019ve now successfully installed Virtualmin! Let\u2019s configure it and create a mailbox.</p><h2>Configuring services and adding your first mailbox</h2><p>First, we need to configure some services. Go to \u2018System Settings\u2019 in the left menu and then to \u2018Features and Plugins\u2019.&nbsp; This is where we disable all services that are not related to serving e-mail. Untick all the boxes I have unticked in this screenshot:</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_017.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4251\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_017\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_017.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_017.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_017-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_017-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>When you click \u2018Save\u2019 you should return to the \u2018System Information\u2019 screen.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_018.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4252\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_018\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_018.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_018.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_018-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_018-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>In the left menu, under \u2018System Settings\u2019, click \u2018Re-Check Configuration\u2019. This should check several things of your installation and display an error is something is wrong.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_019.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4253\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_019\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_019.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_019.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_019-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_019-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Let\u2019s create a Virtual Server, so we can add a mailbox. Click \u2018Create Virtual Server\u2019 in the left menu:</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_020.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4254\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_020\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_020.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_020.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_020-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_020-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Fill out the domain name for the server, which is the domain name you wish to receive e-mail for. Also pick a strong password. Click \u2018Create Server\u2019 to actually create the server:</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_021.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4255\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_021\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_021.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_021.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_021-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_021-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Once your virtual server is up, let\u2019s create a mailbox. Click \u2018Edit Users\u2019 in the left menu, which should open the user list:</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_022.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4256\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_022\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_022.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_022.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_022-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_022-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Clicking \u2018Add a user to this server\u2019 opens the screen to create a new user. Because we disabled several features before, the user you\u2019re going to create will only have an e-mail account. So, basically, you\u2019re creating an e-mail account.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_023.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4257\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_023\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_023.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_023.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_023-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_023-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>Fill out the e-mail address field, a real name and a strong password. Click \u2018Create\u2019 to finish this. You should be returned to the user overview, where you see your newly-created user including the IMAP/POP3 login.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_024.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NzEiIGhlaWdodD0iNTA1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjcxIDUwNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4258\" alt=\"Virtualmin 4.02.gpl on leb001.quateria.net (Ubuntu Linux 12.04.3) - Mozilla Firefox_024\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_024.png.webp\" width=\"671\" height=\"505\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_024.png.webp 1119w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_024-300x225.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Virtualmin-4.02.gpl-on-leb001.quateria.net-Ubuntu-Linux-12.04.3-Mozilla-Firefox_024-1024x770.png.webp 1024w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"></a></p><p>And that\u2019s it! You\u2019ve just created your own e-mail server and your first mailbox!</p><p>To add your mailbox to an e-mail client, like Mozilla Thunderbird, your details will be (from the example above):</p><ul><li>Username: john.smith.example</li><li>Password: the one you picked</li><li>Mail server (IMAP/POP3/SMTP): the domain name/IP of the mail server</li></ul><p>TLS is available but the certificate is self-signed, so you should accept the certificate to enable secure communication with the mail server.</p><p>The final step is to point you domain name\u2019s DNS records to your newly created server, if you didn\u2019t already. If your domain points to the server, point the MX record to your domain. If you\u2019ve used a different domain for your server, point the MX record to that or the server IP. Once the DNS records have propagated, you should be receiving e-mail!</p><h2>Final notes</h2><p>This is one of the easiest ways to get a mail server running. You can improve your server by using a commercial SSL certificate (although, there is word those are not save from government eyes either) and install webmail software. Those are things for a future tutorial, however!</p><p>Your mail server also supports IMAP IDLE, which boils down to push for IMAP. This works especially well with K-9 Mail on an Android device or Mozilla Thunderbird (which both support IMAP IDLE). So, no loss leaving your free e-mail service here!</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Up next week:</span> Getting started with OpenVPN (tap)!</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fyour-own-mail-server-with-virtualmin%2F&amp;t=Your%20own%20mail%20server%20with%20Virtualmin\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-facebook dpsp-no-label dpsp-first\" title=\"Share on Facebook\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Your%20own%20mail%20server%20with%20Virtualmin&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fyour-own-mail-server-with-virtualmin%2F&amp;via=LowEndNetwork\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-twitter dpsp-no-label\" title=\"Share on Twitter\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?url=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fyour-own-mail-server-with-virtualmin%2F&amp;title=Your%20own%20mail%20server%20with%20Virtualmin&amp;mini=true\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-linkedin dpsp-no-label dpsp-last\" title=\"Share on LinkedIn\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li></ul><div class=\"dpsp-total-share-wrapper\"><span class=\"dpsp-icon-total-share\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-total-share-count\">1</span><span>sha